From: Paranoia project (security)
Subject: iOS QPA: honor QT_IM_MODULE (mirror Android pattern)

The iOS platform plugin in Qt 6.10.x hardcodes `m_inputContext = new
QIOSInputContext` and never consults `QPlatformInputContextFactory`. That
makes the QT_IM_MODULE environment variable a no-op on iOS — fields focus
brings up Apple's UITextResponder regardless of whether the user requested
qtvirtualkeyboard. Android/Windows/eglfs all honor the factory; this patch
brings iOS in line.

Paranoia needs Qt Virtual Keyboard to be the *only* input path on iOS for
threat-model reasons (suspected keylogging via Apple's predictive ML
services / third-party keyboards). With QT_IM_MODULE=qtvirtualkeyboard set
in main.cpp, the patched QPA loads VKB as the platform input context and
never instantiates QIOSInputContext, so the native iOS keyboard is not
created. Without QT_IM_MODULE, behavior is unchanged.

License: this file is LGPLv3 (matches qtbase). Patch is a strict mirror of
qandroidplatformintegration.cpp upstream (same QtCompany code).

--- a/src/plugins/platforms/ios/qiosintegration.mm
+++ b/src/plugins/platforms/ios/qiosintegration.mm
@@ -17,6 +17,8 @@
 #include "qiosservices.h"
 #include "qiosoptionalplugininterface.h"

+#include <qpa/qplatforminputcontextfactory_p.h>
+
 #if defined(Q_OS_VISIONOS)
 #include "qiosswiftintegration.h"
 #endif
@@ -91,7 +93,16 @@ void QIOSIntegration::initialize()
 #endif

     // Depends on a primary screen being present
-    m_inputContext = new QIOSInputContext;
+    // Paranoia patch: honor QT_IM_MODULE (mirror of Android QPA pattern).
+    // Upstream iOS QPA hardcodes QIOSInputContext, so QT_IM_MODULE has no
+    // effect — even with qtvirtualkeyboard requested, focus still triggers
+    // the native iOS keyboard via UITextResponder. We need VKB to be the
+    // only input surface (threat model: no system-keyboard keylog path).
+    QStringList icStrs = QPlatformInputContextFactory::requested();
+    icStrs.removeAll(QStringLiteral("ios"));
+    m_inputContext = QPlatformInputContextFactory::create(icStrs);
+    if (!m_inputContext)
+        m_inputContext = new QIOSInputContext;

     QPointingDevice::Capabilities touchCapabilities = QPointingDevice::Capability::Position | QPointingDevice::Capability::NormalizedPosition;
 #if !defined(Q_OS_VISIONOS)
